font-size:12pt"> innovation</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, the path dependency e</span><span style="font-family:'Lucida Grande'; font-size:12pt">ff</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ect tend</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">lock economies into </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">high-carbon research and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">high</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">carbon emissions technologies, even after the introduction of a mild carbon </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">pricing mechanism</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> or </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">research and development</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> subsidies for clean</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> innovation</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.4 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">This highlights the desirability of acting </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">early</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to shift incentives </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">away from </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">dirty</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> innovation and towards low-carbon innovation.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Indeed,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the longer the delay</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, the more </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">difficult and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">expensive it becomes to redirect the economy </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">towards clean technologies</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, as shown by </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Acemoglu</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">et al</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> (2012)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Curr</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ent UK policies </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">are not sufficient</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to move innovation on to a low-carbon pathway and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> this</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">will make</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the UK dependent on foreign technology</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to meet its </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2050 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">emissions reduction </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">target</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> at least cost</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.5 O</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">nce the economy has </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">shifted to a low-carbon </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">innovation pathway</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">path dependency effect </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">implies</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> that the economy then naturally lock</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> itself into </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">low-carbon</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">technologies</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, removing the need for further</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Government support</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">This further strengthens the case for early </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Government </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">action to support </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">low-carbon innovation</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> which can be relaxed in the future as the economy’s stock of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">low-carbon </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">knowledge</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> grows</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">However, c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">lear </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">criteria governing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">future </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">reduc</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">tion</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Government support for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">innovation </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">must be</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> set</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in advance</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to prevent unexpected policy</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> cha</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">nges</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">that</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> could inhibit investment. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The type of support provided for low-carbon innovation in the UK</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.6 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">he UK’s current strategy </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">appears</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to prioriti</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e policies</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">such as</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">feed-in tariffs</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">and a carbon price floor</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">which promote deployment rather than</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">direct support </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">for</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">research and development</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">However, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">as </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">shown</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> by </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Acemoglu</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">et al</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. (2012), </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">environmental polic</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ies</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">that are economically optimal </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to fight climate change not only</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">address demand</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">but also</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">directly incentivi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e the development of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">low-carbon </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">technologies.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.7 Providing more direct support for research and development</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">for</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> low-carbon technologies</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, for example </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">through</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> tax credits</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and subsidies, would provide better value for money and could be economically advantageous for the UK as it is more likely to benefit </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">UK </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">businesses.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Indeed, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">as shown by </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Dechezleprêtre</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&amp;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Glachant</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> (2013),</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">deployment policies </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">incentivi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e innovation activities not </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">just</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">in the UK</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> but also in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">other</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> countries</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. While these deployment policies certainly have a positive impact on</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> global </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">efforts to tackle </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">climate change</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, they </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">may provide less economic benefit to the UK and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">hence may</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> be less poli</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">tically acceptable.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 16.68pt; padding-left:4.62pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">Does the Government have the right balance of focus between energy efficiency,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold"> renewable energy and other low-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">carbon technologies?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">3.1 The best strategy for the UK G</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">overnment </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">is to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">target its </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">support for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">low-carbon innovation </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">at technologies that have the highest </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">potential</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">emissions reduction</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, are </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">furthest away from the market</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">have the highest knowledge </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">spillovers</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> (i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> knowledge</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> benefits for other inventors).</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">3.2 Research by the Grantham Research Institute</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">(</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Dechezle</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">prêtre</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">et al</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, 2013) has shown that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">knowledge </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">spillover</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">benefits </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">(</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">i.e.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the societal benefits that justify policy intervention) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">are much higher in radically new low</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">carbon technologies, such as renewable energy technologies, than in technologies </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">aimed at improving the efficiency of existing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">high-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">carbon tec</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">hnologies. This justifies prioriti</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ing renewable energy technologies, in particular the most radically new </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">technologies </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">(</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">for example</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">off</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">shore </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">wind</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> marine energy), over energy efficiency techn</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ologies</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 16.68pt; padding-left:4.62pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">What outcomes, if any, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">is</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold"> the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">Low</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">Carbon Innovation Coordination Group</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">(</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">LCICG</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold"> likely to achieve? How should its forthcoming strategy drive more investment into low</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">carbon innovation, and how should it measure success?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">4</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">1 Th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> measurement of success</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">important to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> sustain </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">G</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">overnment support </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">for</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the LCICG</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">R</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">esearchers at</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the Grantham Research Institute have </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">developed three</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">indicators that can be used</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> at the national level</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to assess the success of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">low-carbon innovation</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> UK:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Patent applications filed by UK businesses </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">for</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> low-carbon technologies, both in the UK and elsewhere. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">One benefit</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">using </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">patent applications </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">as a metric is that they allow the identification of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> low-carbon technologies </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">at a highly disaggregated leve</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">l</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e.g.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> wave energy patents)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">of their link to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> UK-based applicants</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Exports of low-ca</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">rbon capital goods from the UK (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e,g</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> wind turbines</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">So far w</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e have identified about 20 different low-carbon capital goods that we are able to trace in international t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">rade databases</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Foreign investments in UK-based low-carbon </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">businesses and, conversely, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">investments </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">made by</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">UK-based low-carbon </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">businesses </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> foreign countries, are </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">another</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">good indicator </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the success </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> any low-carbon innovation strategy</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">4.2 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Two of these indicators seem already </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to be </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">part of the metrics</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> used by the LCICG</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. We </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">recommend that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">international </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">investment indicator should be added.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">4.3 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Ideally</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> LCICG </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">sh</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ould try to measure not only the impact of low-carbon innovation policies </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">on the growth of the low-carbon sector</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, but also the impact of these policies on the growth of the economy as a whole. A key result from </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">recent research by the Grantham Research Institute </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">is that a redirection of innovation from </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">dirty</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">low-carbon </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">techn</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ologies can lead to higher economic growth in the medium</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> term</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> because </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">low-carbon </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">technologies generate much larger knowledge spillovers in the economy than the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">dirty</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> technologie</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s they replace (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Dechezleprêtre</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">et al</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, 2013). A necessary condition for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">low-c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">arbon </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">policies </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">impact</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">growth of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the economy </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">more broadly </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">is that</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">technologies</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> they support</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">must </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">generate</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">benefits</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> outside their </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">own fields</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">4.4 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">For </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">example</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Dechezleprêtre</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">et al</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> (2013) found that clean patents in the car industry relating to the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">generation,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> conversion or distribution of electric power</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> have been </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">used to develop new computer sciences patents in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">electrical digital data processing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> technologies. Another example is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">combustion apparatus using fluent fuel</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> technologies</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, which</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> hav</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> spi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ll</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ed </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">over</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">diagnosis, surgery and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> identification</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">patents</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in medical science.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Grantham Research Institute is</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> currently </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">working on a project that analyses</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the impact of knowledge spillovers from green technologies on business performance.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> This methodology could be applied to UK businesses</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in particular to measure the impact of low-carbon innovation on economic growth.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">This project seems </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">very relevant for the work of the LCICG</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, and its</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> results will be available in Spring/Summer 2014.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 16.68pt; padding-left:4.62pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">How </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">should DECC ensure that its remaining capital allocation for low</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">carbon innovation will be spent wisely, after two years of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">underspend</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">5.1 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">DECC should </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">prioritises innovation</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">funding for</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">carbon capture and storage (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">CCS</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> technologies.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">5.2 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Given the current energy mix in the UK, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">support for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">CCS</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> (including gas, industrial and biomass CCS)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> will be a key component of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the Government’s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">strategy for achieving the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">target</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> reduc</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">greenhouse gas</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">emissions by 80% </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">by</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> 2050</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> compared with</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> 1990 levels</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> In addition, CCS technologies are still at an early stage of development</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">; when</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">G</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ov</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ernment support is most needed.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">5.3 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In a recent paper, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Dechezleprêtre</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">et al</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">(</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2013) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">f</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ou</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">nd that innovations in CCS technologies generate even larger knowledge </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">spillovers</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">than renewable energy technologies, implying that the incentives to conduct private research and development activities</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, compared to what is socially desirable, are lower</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">for CCS</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> than </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">for</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">other technologies (including </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">renewables</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">S</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">trong public support is</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">therefore</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> warranted.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">References</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Acemoglu</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, D., </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Aghion</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, P., </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Bursztyn</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, L., and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Hemous</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, D.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2012</span><span style="font-family:Ar